definitions.definition: To bite or chew loudly or heavily.
examples: The dog chomped on the treat and swallowed it in one gulp.

definitions.definition: To remove the final character from (a text string ) if it is a newline (or, less commonly, some other programmer-specified character).

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To bite or chew loudly or heavily.
secondary_definitions: ( computing , transitive , Perl ) To remove the final character from (a text string ) if it is a newline (or, less commonly, some other programmer-specified character).
